==Demographics==
At the [[2020 United States Census|2020 census]] and [[American Community Survey|2023 Community Survey 5-year estimates]] there were 2,179 people and 921 households living in the CDP. The population density was {{convert|702.9|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 921 housing units at an average density of {{convert|297.1|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}.  The [[Race and ethnicity in the United States Census#2000 census|racial makeup]] of the CDP was 90.55% White, 1.01% African American, 0.18% Native American, 0.46% Asian, 0.64% from other races, and 7.16% from two or more races. Hispanic or Latino of any race were 1.51%.<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|access-date=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref>

Of the 734 households 17.3% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 44.7% were married couples living together, 35.2% had a female householder with no husband, and 11.6% had a male householder with no spouse present. The average household size was 3.18.

The age distribution was 17.6% under the age of 18, 4.8% from 18 to 24, 46.8% from 25 to 44, 21.5% from 45 to 64, and 11.1% 65 or older. The median age was 34.7 years.

The median household income was $62,011. About 9.6% of the population were below the [[poverty line]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/profile/Susquehanna_Trails_CDP,_Pennsylvania?g=160XX00US4275574 |website=data.census.gov |access-date=27 May 2025}}</ref>

